additional_info.race_comment: WHERE'S JOHNSON (4) quickly into stride to win over the 520m at this track two runs back then prominent throughout when finishing second at this track last start. Has a quick 30.07 PB at this course and distance. Expected to feature in the finish again. MASTER DISTILLER (1) was favourite last start and led all the way, scoring by 0.8 lengths (30.35) at this track in a Novice race over 520m. Deserves serious consideration again. BORA BLUE (8) has been mixing form lately, hitting the frame two back before finishing fourth (31.34) at Ipswich in a Grade 4/5. Expecting significant improvement this line-up. BLUE JANGLES (3) is worth consideration after filling a hole last start.

form_summary.entrantComment: Didn't make the placings last time at this track (31.03) in a Grade 5, finishing a 12 length fifth. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minors. Can feature in the finish.
Inside draw could be an advantage. Last start finished seventh in a Grade 5 on July 10 over 520m at this track behind Excessive, beaten 20 lengths (31.61). Major threat on best form.
Recent form has been ordinary and he is facing a tougher line up. Looks outclassed here.
Is back up to 520m which has been an issue in the past. Last appeared when third over 366m at Capalaba five days ago. No easier here so may struggle.
Jumped well at Ipswich two runs back then again settled forward and finished second at Ipswich last start over 431m. Should be around the mark.
Hit the ground running last time with a hot early split and tried to lead throughout but had to settle for the minors when second (30.16) at this track. In form and can return to the winners' list.
Flew the lids with a slick early split last time and went on to clock 30.35 as a strongly fancied winner over 520m at this track. Can win again.

Found some support last start but struggled and finished 4th over 520m at Ipswich beaten 7 lengths (31.34) behind Japanese Black in a Grade 4/5 on July 8. Placed two back at Ipswich. Thereabouts of late and rates highly this line-up. Expected to be in the finish.
